69.6	Zazen	Zazen	In Zen Buddhism, zazen (literally "seated meditation"; Japanese: ; simplified Chinese: ; traditional Chinese: ; pinyin: zuò chán; Wade–Giles: tso4-ch'an2) is a meditative discipline practitioners perform to calm the body and the mind, and be able to concentrate enough to experience insight into the nature of existence and thereby gain enlightenment.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Zazen_au_Centre_Europ%C3%A9en_du_Zen_Rinzai.jpg/220px-Zazen_au_Centre_Europ%C3%A9en_du_Zen_Rinzai.jpg
